One person is feared dead and scores injured after the driver of a mini-bus matatu lost control and plunged into a ditch along Waiyaki Way in Nairobi. The Metro mini-bus was headed to town from Kikuyu and the driver is said to have lost control at Kangemi. The vehicle veered off the road near the fly-over and fell into a ditch full of water. Rescue operations are underway as reports indicate some passengers and the crew of the matatu are still trapped in the car. Those rescued have been rushed to Kenyatta National Hospital for treatment.  More to follow    